&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;STAFF NURSE - &lt;strong&gt;BAND 5  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;23 HOURS PER WEEK – 2 X 11.5 HOURS SHIFTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Internal rotation Days and Nights.&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A great opportunity has arisen to work in our new Hospital, which is a 24 bedded unit providing intermediate and palliative care facilities to the local community.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We require innovative, enthusiastic and motivated individual to join our team.  You will be required to plan, implement, evaluate and take responsibility for the nursing care of the ward patients.  You will have a flexible approach to working and be willing to participate in the development of the wards.  You should have a minimum 12 months experience following qualification of RGN.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Charlotte Champion – Ward Manager on 01684 612634.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
